"Software" refers to the MarkEnti project and all included code, documentation, and related materials.
"You" refers to the user or company or other legal entity utilizing the Software.
"License" refers to this license agreement, or another written agreement between you and the copyright holder for the Software.
"Non-Commercial Use" means utilizing the Software for personal, educational, research, or internal use within non-profit organizations without direct financial gain.
"Commercial Use" means any use of the Software, directly or as part of a larger work, in a revenue-generating context. This includes, but is not limited to:
Selling or licensing the Software or works derived from it.
Using the Software to provide services to clients.
Incorporating the Software into products offered for sale or license.
