Improvements:

Expanded "Commercial Use" Definition: Outlines typical scenarios for better understanding of what constitutes commercial use.
Derivative Works: Clarifies that they are permitted under the non-commercial license, with conditions.
Discretionary Licensing: Emphasizes that the copyright holder retains control over granting commercial licenses.
Additional Considerations:

Jurisdiction: You might want to specify the governing law/jurisdiction for this license.
Attribution: Consider requiring attribution to your project, even for non-commercial use.